The West African Examination Council (WAEC), on Friday in Lagos, announced the release of results for schools based candidates for the 2019 West African Senior School Certificate Examinations (WASSCE). According to the council, the results showed a 64. 18 per cent performance for candidates that obtained 5 credits and above in a minimum of five subjects including English language and Mathematics. The Head of Nigeria National office of WAEC, Mr. Olu Adenipekun disclosed this to newsmen at the headquarters of the Council in Lagos. “Of this number, 507, 862 that is 49.77 per cent male candidates, and 512,657 that is 50.23 per cent were female candidates.
The percentage of candidates in this category in the WASSCE for school candidates, 2018 was 50 per cent. Details later…